Watch the movie “Escape from Alcatraz” with Clint Eastwood.

[quote=“pko, post:6, topic:21177”]OMFG SRSLY?!?!

just fucking tell it.

its an islands where the kept hardcore killing basterds, no one got loose and they pwned noobs.

Write on that.[/quote]
???

Alcatraz is a prison island in San Francisco. It was made to be inescapable. Very very few people ever escaped. One man escaped temporarily but was pretty much killed by the Golden Gate. Another guy tried to slip away on an army boat, but the person in charge found he had an extra man on board and phoned Alcatraz, and I think there was another one.

Here is a nice link to help you.
http://www.notfrisco2.com/alcatraz/faq/faq1.html

~Ron

item.dc:creator: @airforce525 airforce525
item.description:
@airforce525 wrote:

An essay on alkatraz
In order to understand our selves, we must first understand alkatraz. Underestimate alkatraz at your peril. While it is becoming a hot topic for debate, spasmodically it returns to create a new passion amongst those who study its history. It is estimated that that alkatraz is thought about eight times every day by the easily lead, many of whom blame the influence of television. In the light of this I will break down the issues in order to give each of them the thought that they fully deserve

Social Factors

Comparisons between Roman Society and Medieval Society give a clear picture of the importance of alkatraz to developments in social conduct. I will not insult the readers inteligence by explaining this obvious comparison any further. When Lance Bandaner said ‘twelve times I’ve traversed the ocean of youthful ambition but society still collects my foot prints’ [1] he could have been making a reference to alkatraz, but probably not. No symbol is more potent than alkatraz in society today. It cleary plays a significant role amongst the developing middle classes.

When one is faced with people of today a central theme emerges - alkatraz is either adored or despised, it leaves no one undecided. If society has a favourite child, it is alkatraz.

Economic Factors

Economics has been defined as ‘I’ll scratch your back if you scratch mine.’ To my learned ear that sounds like two people with itchy backs. We will study the Spanish-Armada model, a classic economic system of analysis. Cost
Of
Living

alkatraz

The results displayed in the graph are too clear to be ignored. Recent studies indicate that the cost of living will eventually break free from the powerful influence of alkatraz, but not before we see a standardised commercial policy for all. A sharp down turn in middle class investment may lead to changes in the market.

Political Factors

Politics - smolitics! Comparing current political thought with that held just ten years ago is like comparing the two, equally popular approaches to alkatraz. If the reader is unaware of these, they need only to turn on the television, or pick up a newspaper or popular magazine.

Take a moment to consider the words of that most brilliant mind Demetrius Rock ‘A man must have his cake and eat it in order to justify his actions.’ [2] Primarily, he is referring to alkatraz. History tells us that alkatraz will always be a vote winner, whether we like it, or not.

Is alkatraz politically correct, in every sense? Each man, woman and to a lesser extent, child, must make up their own mind.
Conclusion

How much responsibility lies with alkatraz? We can say that alkatraz is both a need and a want. It enriches, provides financial security and figures show it’s a winning formular.

Here with the final word is Hollywood’s Macaulay Morissette: ‘alkatraz is the new rock and roll! And the new opera!’ [3]

[1] Lance Bandaner - Adventurous Spirit - 1993 See-Saw Publishing

[2] Rock - Roll It Up - 1977 - F. Lower Publishing

[3] Your guide to alkatraz - Issue 98 - T36 Publishing
